Configurating PGPRMail:
=======================

    Usually, PGPRMail does @{i}not@{ui} need any configuration. However, it
checks out the following keywords in either @{b}S:UUConfig@{ub} or @{b}UULIB:Config@{ub}:

@{b}Debug@{ub}
     Here, you can set the amount of debugging output, PGPRMail shall
     write to the logfile. The higher the number is, the more output is
     provided.  Default is @{b}0@{ub}.

@{b}Lockdir@{ub}
     Here you can choose the directory, the UUCP-package shall create
     the temporary files for file-access-syncronization in. Default is
     @{b}T:@{ub}.


@EndNode

@Node "PRM_Log messages" "PGP_MIP.guide/PRM_Log messages"
@Next "PRM_Future releases"
@Prev "PRM_Configuration"
@Toc "PGPRMail"

What logfile entries does PGPRMail generate and what do they mean?
==================================================================

    my_ulog(4, "PGPRMail, started with commandline `%s'", argv);

    my_ulog(4, "PGPRMail, loglevel is %d", LogLevel);

    my_ulog(-1, "PGPRMail, %s", message);

    my_ulog(1, "PGPRMail, starting '%s'", line);

    my_ulog(2, "PGPRMail, encrypted block in '%s'", PIPE2);

    my_ulog(2, "PGPRMail, modified mail in '%s'", PIPE1);

    my_ulog(2, "PGPRMail, original mail in '%s'", FILENAME);

    my_ulog(2, "PGPRMail, starting '%s'", line);

    my_ulog(3, "PGPRMail, found \"%s\"", MSG_BEGIN);

    my_ulog(3, "PGPRMail, found \"%s\"", MSG_END);

    my_ulog2(-1, "PGPRMail, decrypting process failed");

    my_ulog2(1, "PGPRMail, mail is routed to another machine and
therefore not decrypted");

    my_ulog2(1, "PGPRMail, no parameters provided -> TERMINATED");

    my_ulog2(1, "PGPRMail, PGP failed somehow");

    my_ulog2(2, "PGPRMail, decrypted text joined to mail-body");


@EndNode

@Node "PRM_Future releases" "PGP_MIP.guide/PRM_Future releases"
@Next "PRM_System requirements"
@Prev "PRM_Log messages"
@Toc "PGPRMail"

What is planned for future version?
===================================

    PGPRMail proved to be very reliable in an exhaustive beta-testing
phase, so I doubt that I will have many bugs to fix or features to add
in the near future.

    The only thing worth improving is the way PGP is controlled. At the
moment you need @{i}PGPPASS@{ui} (see @{"system requirements" Link "PRM_System requirements"}) set in order to make
PGP decrypt anything.

    However, I'm planning to add a routine to PGPRMail, that pops up a
requester and asks the user for the password, submitting the result to
PGP via the commandline.

    Also I'm thinking about opening a console-window for PGP, so the
user can see what is going on and can possibly control PGP interactivly.


@EndNode

@Node "PRM_System requirements" "PGP_MIP.guide/PRM_System requirements"
@Prev "PRM_Future releases"
@Toc "PGPRMail"

What do I need to run PGPRMail?
===============================

   - Your Amiga shoud be running KICKSTART 1.2 or later. Also at least
     one megabyte memory should be available.

   - You must have PGP v2.2 or later installed. Earlier version miss
     the @{i}+batchmode@{ui} flag, also as the possibility to en-/decrypt
     messages for multiple receipients.

     "Installed" means, that PGP is in your commandpath so PGPRMail can
     call it to handle the decryption-stuff.

     If you have problems with PGP leaving files in your @{b}UUSpool:@{ub},
     check our if PGP's @{b}KeepBinary@{ub} option is turned off.

   - You must set the enviroment variable @{i}PGPPASS@{ui}, otherwise PGPRMail
     won't be able to decrypt anything. See @{"Things to do" Link "PRM_Future releases"}.

   - You must have @{b}T:@{ub} assigned, because all temporary files go into @{b}T:@{ub}.


@EndNode

