@Node "PST_What is it?" "PGP_MIP.guide/PST_What is it?"
@Next "PST_Installation"
@Toc "PGPSignText"

What is PGPSignText?
====================

    PGPSignText is a small utility to sign textfiles using PGP in a
simple way. In fact, it does nothing but copying the specified file
into a temporary file, calling PGP to sign it, and replacing the signed
file with the original.

    Maybe this effect could simply have been archived with a simple
CShell-alias or a small ARexx-script, but usually people like to have
it as simple as possible. :-)


@EndNode

@Node "PST_Installation" "PGP_MIP.guide/PST_Installation"
@Next "PST_Usage"
@Prev "PST_What is it?"
@Toc "PGPSignText"

How to install PGPSignText:
===========================

    PGPSignText does not require a special installation. Just copy the
executable somewhere into your commandpath.

    PGPSignText does - of course - require PGP to be installed correctly
and @{i}PGPPASS@{ui} to be set, or it won't be able to sign anything.


@EndNode

@Node "PST_Usage" "PGP_MIP.guide/PST_Usage"
@Prev "PST_Installation"
@Toc "PGPSignText"

Usage:
======

    PGPSignText requires only one parameter, the name of the textfile to
sign.


@EndNode

